#作文(timing: 50, words: 205, date: "2025-12-08")[Beechwood Farm is surrounded by country road to the north-west and a winding river in the south, which crosses the coutry road and flows south-east ward before it bends up north again.

In the 1950s, the farm was divided by a field track in the middle. Between the track and the river lied, from west to the east, a fruit trees field, a soft fruits field, a vegetables field, and a living area which contained a chikens pen, a farmhouse, and a barn by the side of the track. To the north of the track is a pasture for sheep.

But today, Beechwood Farm has changed in quite a few places. First, the field track is upgraded to become roads. There is a new farm shop in the fruit trees field just beside the road. The old barn is converted to holiday cottages, and a new, smaller barn is added, connecting to the road. In what used to be the sheep pasture lie a camping field in the west where tents are made under the shade of a nice groove, and a power field in the east where many solar panels are erected. Both new fields come with a parking lot connected to the road.]